name: Ampisallen
description: Alexander Helander is a Swedish adaptive wakeboard rider who competes in the seated wakeboard category, a parasport discipline of wakeboarding that allows athletes with lower-body disabilities to ride in a seated position. He has represented Sweden at international cable wakeboard events under the governance of the International Waterski & Wakeboard Federation (IWWF). Alexander uses adaptive equipment and teams with advocates for active lifestyles for people with disabilities. As an adaptive athlete, he appears on social media as @ampisallen, where he shares his experiences in wakeboarding and other adaptive sports, promoting accessibility and inclusivity. Alexander has competed in European and World seated wakeboard competitions, participating in the World Cable Wakeboard & Wakeskate Championship and the Wakeboard Seated Open Men category at major IWWF events. He continues to be active within the adaptive wakeboard community and is involved in spreading awareness of adaptive sports opportunities.

name: GeorgeHunt001
description: George Hunt is a British BMX racer from England competing at national and international BMX racing events. Known online as @george1.1, he is a competitive BMX cyclist riding in the Superclass / Elite U23 categories with the Ice Bikes UK Factory Team. Hunt was the British U23 National Champion in 2024 and has featured on podiums in British BMX National Series events. He gained recognition as one of the top junior elite BMX racers in Great Britain, including finishing as #2 junior elite nationally and being a multiple Midlands Regional BMX elite champion. George has also competed internationally at European BMX Cup races where he raced in U23 Men‚Äôs fields. He regularly shares racing highlights, training, and season announcements on social media, including renewed seasons with his racing team. In addition to national competitions, George has traveled to international BMX events and has aspirations toward higher UCI and Olympic level competition. Known for his speed, bike handling skills, and competitive spirit, he continues to develop within BMX racing circuits.
